The paper deals with a matrix recovery problem and involves the estimation of deviation of the sum of matrices from its expected value. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of operator norm and Chernoff-bound, which are concepts commonly used in the fields of Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) and Statistics (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves a classical argument by Hoeffding, which is a well-known concept in the field of Data Structures (cs.DS).
